This time of year as it winds down to its last days is the perfect moment to reflect back over the past year’s experiences and set your intentions for the year ahead.  The word of year for me was ‘transformative’- filled with challenges & personal growth.  I felt the need for change deeply for so many reasons & it came with divine timing.  But let me tell you it was work, real deep soul level, grinding work. But I am so proud that I surrounded myself with incredible mentors in this exciting chapter of my professional journey. 

In 2023 I plan to take all the skills I have learned over the years & @ubcsauderschool to step further into what is a job opportunity of a lifetime.  I’m incredibly proud to announce that I am a Partner at @teammcknightre, a company that has sold $620 million in sales in the last three years, $2.2 billion in total.  I’m so excited to help write the next chapter of our company - adding new pages to an already incredible story.  To those of you that have followed & supported me on this journey I’m incredibly grateful for your trust & positive energy.  I also do recognize the privilege of this position, and will continue to advocate for equal opportunities & rights for women & our LGTBQ community, especially in our BIPOC community.  I promise I have so much more work to do in making our collective voices be heard.  I look forward to continuing to serve my community for their residential, investment, commercial, & project marketing real estate needs.

I have never been more grateful, excited, and at peace than ever before in my life.  I have some big plans for 2023, starting this next year with gratitude.

What a full circle moment I experienced this International Women’s Day ⭕️. UBC is the most prestigious University in British Columbia, a world class education facility that I dreamed of attending growing up.  I remember being 18 and I had just graduated highschool & I excitedly applied to their business program along with other universities and eagerly awaited my acceptance letter. Unfortunately, my application wasn’t accepted, and I eventually attended another university for my Business and Marketing degree. 

Decades passed, I built a business and had a family, and eventually returned to doors of UBC, this time years later to complete my studies & obtain my Real Estate License, and I made the transition from lipsticks to listings!  My 18 year old self would have never believed that I would be invited to UBC, but this time as a keynote speaker.  I am beyond honoured & humbled to have been invited by UBC @ubcaus’s International Women’s Day dinner.  I shared the stage with some incredible women and shared my struggles as a woman in business, but also as a South Asian woman with a full room of students with a completely open heart.  Education is a human right should be available to women around the world.  It is the key to breaking oppression of women globally.  I was also so proud to share the stage with friend and bossbabe @ravthechef @justcakesbakeshop who also attended UBC and shared her incredible professional journey!  A big thank you to my @teammcknightre family & friends for coming out to support!  I left inspired and energized by the event and I hope the students enjoyed our shared stories & experiences. 

To hear my full speech check out my ‘UBC x SM’ highlight reel!
